      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Instead of dismissing the United Nations report on Guant치namo, the Bush administration should accept its recommendations and close the prison camp.</p>
        <p>Human rights and political pragmatism are not incompatible. To survive and prosper, the United States must recapture its leadership in human rights, which it so effectively used in the 1940's when it was the primary mover in creating the United Nations and the Universal Declaration of Human Rights to promote fundamental freedoms -- especially freedom from fear, but also freedom from want, freedom of religion and freedom of speech.</p>
        <p>Evelyne Shuster  Wallingford, Pa., Feb. 17, 2006</p>
      </block>
